data.name: Roasted Tomato Basil Soup
data.quickTastyDescription: A comforting and creamy soup made with roasted tomatoes and fresh basil, perfect for dipping or sipping!
detailedCookingInstructions: Cut the tomatoes in half and place them on a baking sheet. Add quartered onion and garlic cloves to the sheet. Drizzle with olive oil and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Roast in the oven for about 25 minutes, until the tomatoes are caramelized and tender.
Once roasted, transfer the tomatoes, onions, and garlic to a blender or pot. Add the fresh basil leaves and vegetable broth.
Blend until smooth or use an immersion blender in the pot to puree the soup to your desired consistency.
Heat the soup on the stove over medium heat, and stir in heavy cream if using. Adjust seasoning with salt and pepper as needed.
Serve hot, garnished with extra basil leaves or a drizzle of olive oil.
data.modifiersForBase: Roasted and blended for a rich flavor
